      "side": 1,
      "message": "I just saw this come through status and it\u0027s not 100% the right way to do this, based on how the layout FP returns values to the main gradient FP. The layout t is stored in the returned \"color\"\u0027s x channel, and the returned color\u0027s y channel is used as a discard flag for complex gradients (two-point conical). \n\nAt the moment, it just so happens that we tend to return y \u003d 0 for the other layouts, and most colorizers don\u0027t depend on the y channel of their coord. The exception to this is texture-based one, which samples by xy now. Since we always bind a texture with h\u003d1, there shouldn\u0027t be any real change between the likely y \u003d 0, and original y \u003d 0.5.\n\nIn a follow up CL it would be good to just have the clamp/tile gradient effects sample their colorizer FP at t.x0 instead of t.xy so that there isn\u0027t a future risk of contamination from layout to colorizer.",
